|(x,y)|= \sqrt{\langle x,x\rangle}\sqrt{\langle y,y\rangle}.
\begin{align} \sqrt{\langle x,x\rangle}\sqrt{\langle y,y\rangle}&=\sqrt{\langle\lambda y,\lambda y\rangle}\sqrt{\langle y,y\rangle} \\ &= \sqrt{\lambda \langle y,\lambda y\rangle}\sqrt{\langle y,y\rangle} \\  &= \sqrt{\lambda^2 \langle y, y\rangle}\sqrt{\langle y,y\rangle} \\ &= \sqrt{( \lambda \langle y, y\rangle)^2} \\ &= |\lambda|\langle y, y\rangle \quad \text{and because of the positive axiom we get that} \\ &= |\lambda ( y, y)|= |(x, y)| \end{align}
